ABANDON NO-ABANDON "NO ABANDON"

Usage:  abandon [target/coordinates] [confirm]
        manage no-abandon

This command allows you to abandon a building or tile of land which your 
empire no longer wants. This falls under the cede privilege. Buildings and rare
crops require you to type 'confirm' when you try to abandon them remotely.

It can also be used to abandon vehicles.

If you use 'manage' to set a tile as no-abandon, you must add the 'confirm'
to abandon it. Workforce chores like abandon-chopped will not abandon these
tiles.

Privileged immortals can abandon rooms and vehicles they do not own.

See also: CEDE, CLAIM, MANAGE, PRIVILEGE, PUBLICIZE
#
ALLIANCE "DIPLOMACY ALLIANCE" ALLY ALLIES ALLIED

Usage:  diplomacy alliance <empire>

When two empires form an alliance, they gain full access to each other's lands,
buildings, and portals. Allies can also pick up items on the ground, and can
lead non-allied players into their allies' lands.

Guards and guard towers will never attack their own allies.

The exchange rate in an alliance is 75%.

You can break an alliance by declaring distrust.

See also: DIPLOMACY, DISTRUST
