DISMANTLE-MINES "DISMANTLE MINES"

The dismantle-mines workforce chore will automatically mark mines to be
dismantled when they are empty. However, workers will only dismantle it if the
building chore is turned on as well. You can prevent dismantling of individual
mines using the nodismantle command.

Mines must be dismantled when empty in order for the ore to refresh.

See also: NODISMANTLE, WORKFORCE
#
DISTRUST "DIPLOMACY DISTRUST" DISTRUSTFUL

Usage:  diplomacy distrust <empire>
        eedit frontiertraits <add | remove> distrustful
        city traits <city> <add | remove> distrustful

When an empire distrusts you, their guards and guard towers will attack you on
sight. Most offenses, including infiltrating your buildings or killing your
citizens, will automatically trigger a state of distrust.

If you declare distrust with the 'diplomacy' command, your empire will always
be hostile to members of the other empire.

If you set the 'distrustful' trait on your cities or frontier, your guards will
be hostile to neutral players (ones with no diplomatic relationship, or where
you have a truce but not peace with them).

If your empire is not distrustful, your guards will not attack neutral players.
The distrustful setting also won't work within 75 tiles of a starting location
(Tower of Souls).

The exchange rate with distrust is 25%.

See also: DIPLOMACY, PEACE, TRUCE
