HOME "HOME STORAGE"

Usage:  home [set/unset/list/clear]
        home inventory [item keywords]
        home identify <item keywords>
        home retrieve [number] [item keywords]
        home store [number] <item keywords>

You can choose a house in your empire to make your own private residence. Once
you set it as your home, other members of the empire can't enter (except the
highest-ranking leaders). You can unset your home from anywhere, or clear the
owner for the building you're in. Only the empire leaders can clear homes they
don't own.

Any member may type "home list" to see all homes in the empire.

You can store up to 300 unique items -- items that can't be stored in other
buildings -- in your home. Identical items stack with each other and don't
count toward that 300. When you move to a new home, you can access your stored
items from your new home after 1 hour. You can check your home inventory and
identify its items from anywhere. Perishable items will continue to decay in
home storage, but only while you're in the game (just like your inventory).

Only buildings that normally house citizens can be set as homes. This does not
include buildings where adding a bedroom grants a citizen, if the building
itself doesn't house citizens.

Immortals can check a player's home storage using: home inventory <player>

See also: AUTOSTORE, CITIZENS, HESTIAN TRINKET
