RECLAIM RECLAIMED

Usage:  reclaim [direction]

This command can be used to take ownership of a tile from another empire. You
must be standing on or adjacent to the tile and must already own 4 or more
adjacent tiles. You must also meet at least one of these three criteria:
- You are at war with the other empire
- You have a city on the island and the other empire doesn't
- The tile is in one of your established cities, but is not in a city or
  outskirts for the other empire

If you reclaim from an adjacent tile, you must own that tile and it must be
open/outdoors. The other empire will be alerted to your location.

Reclaiming will take a little while and can be interrupted by combat. All
players can attack you while you're reclaiming. You will cause an offense
against the other empire for reclaiming a tile.

Reclaiming a tile requires the 'claim' privilege. Reclaiming while not at war
also requires the 'diplomacy' privilege.

