"TERRITORY COMMAND"

Usage:  territory [options] [keywords] [-exclude keyword]

The territory command will list all your territory. This command groups tiles
that are near each other so that it shows you fewer lines.

Supported options:
   -cities   Only tiles in cities.
   -outskirts   Only tiles on outskirts.
   -frontier   Only tiles on the frontier.
   -distance N   Only locations within N tiles of you.
   -island "name"   Only locations on the given island (use quotes if needed).
   -no-abandon   Only no-abandon tiles.
   -no-dismantle   Only no-dismantle tiles.
   -no-work   Only no-work tiles.
   -public   Only public tiles.

You can also add search keywords. Starting a keyword with a dash (-) will
search for tiles that DON'T have that word. If you need to exclude a word
such as "island" which is also a search option, use two dashes (--island).
You can specify multiple keywords at once.

Interior rooms, such as bedrooms, are only searched if keywords are given.
Otherwise, this command only searches map tiles.

You require the Navigation ability to use the "territory" command, because it
gives coordinates.

Immortals may provide an empire name as the first argument. Use quotes if it's
more than 1 word.

See also: CITIES, CITY COMMAND, NAVIGATION, TERRITORY, MANAGE
