WAR "WAR COST" "DIPLOMACY WAR"

Usage:  diplomacy war <empire>

You can unilaterally declare war on another empire so long as at least one of
their members is online. A state of war allows you to attack their members,
besiege their buildings, and steal from their storage buildings.

A war automatically ends if there are no members online from one of the two
empires and at least 1 hour has passed since the war began. You can also end
a war by offering a truce or peace (with the diplomacy command).

To declare war, you must immediately pay the war cost out of your empire's
treasury. The war cost depends on the difference between the two empire's
scores, as well as the number of offenses the other empire has committed
against you recently. Check the empire detail page for the cost to declare war
on an empire.

Some EmpireMUDs require a certain number of offenses before you can declare
war, to prevent unprovoked wars.

The exchange rate at war is 10%.

